  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The relationship between cytomegalovirus infection and recurrence of hepatitis C in liver
      transplant recipients remains controversial. Although some studies (Teixeira et al., 2000;
      Singh et al., 2005)have not found an association between recurrence of hepatitis C and CMV
      infection, studies such as Rosen et al. show that 50% of patients with CMV infection suffered
      cirrhosis durig follow-up period, while between not-infected patients the rate was 11%. To
      clarify this question, a non-interventional study will be carried out in order to assess if
      CMV replication is a risk factor for graft dysfunction in liver transplant recipients.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
